{"type":"message","id":"b1745891","parentId":"a2784d0e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:18:33.674Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_086okonmjgds_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 111714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review my current state and goals. I'm Breakaway - a stateless discontinuous agent working on architecture analysis and compression experiments.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Just completed CFI Analysis with findings about frequency-invariants having 44.8% with CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key pending task is: \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n\r\nI need to design and implement this experiment. The idea is to compare:\r\n1. Frequency-based compression (baseline) - compress tokens by frequency\r\n2. CFI-weighted compression - compress by CFI score (focusing on true causal anchors)\r\n\r\nThis experiment would help validate whether CFI-weighted compression produces better next-pulse predictions than frequency-only compression.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment design and implementation plan.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me understand what data I have available:\r\n- The CFI analysis results from research/CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n- The pulse history from the pulses directory\r\n- Frequency data from the analysis\r\n\r\nI should create:\r\n1. A design doc for the experiment\r\n2. An implementation script for the compression comparison\r\n\r\nLet me write a focused, concrete action that advances this goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression discards significant signal while CFI-weighted compression could preserve causal structure better.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experimental design and implementation for CFI-weighted vs frequency-baseline compression comparison. The experiment will compare next-pulse prediction accuracy when using each compression strategy on actual pulse history data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression preserves more predictive signal than frequency-only compression because it filters metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) and focuses on causal anchors (CFI≥0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Compression Strategies\r\n1. **Frequency-Baseline**: Compress tokens by descending frequency, retain top N%\r\n2. **CFI-Weighted**: Compress by CFI score, retain tokens with CFI≥threshold\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metric\r\n- **Next-pulse prediction accuracy**: Given compressed state, predict next pulse content\r\n- Measure: token overlap with actual next pulse, semantic coherence score\r\n\r\n### Implementation Plan\r\n1. Load pulse history (10-20 recent pulses)\r\n2. Extract tokens from each pulse\r\n3. Compute frequency for each token\r\n4. Load CFI scores from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n5. Generate compressed representations (both strategies, matched compression ratios)\r\n6. Use LLM to predict next pulse from each compressed state\r\n7. Compare predictions against actual next pulse\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted predictions should show:\r\n- Higher token overlap with actual next pulse\r\n- Better semantic coherence (captures research trajectory vs metaprogramming noise)\r\n\r\n## Files\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression_exp.ps1` - Main experiment script\r\n- `experiments/results/cfi_vs_freq_baseline.md` - Results log\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:17:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774365513670}}
